    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-22T09:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-22T09:35:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/1180: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-22T18:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 22, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 22—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>449. Bill to repeal Millspaugh economic powers was introduced into Majlis today.
                    It is to be discussed at one secret session in next 2 days and vote taken on
                    June 25. Friendly Majlis Deputy has told Millspaugh only miracle can prevent
                    passage.</p>
                <p>Millspaugh is determined to resign but undecided whether to do so immediately or
                    await passage of bill. He says he has no idea how many members of mission will
                    follow suit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
